Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.ReturnReference: Description of Uncertain Tax Positions Under FIN 48:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: The Organization is exempt from federal income tax as an entity described in Internal Revenue Code (IRC) Section 501(c)(3) except to the extent of unrelated business taxable income as defined under IRC Sections 511 through 515. Effective July 1, 2009, the Organization adopted accounting for uncertain tax positions. The accounting standard prescribes a recognition threshold and measurement process for uncertain tax positions. As of June 30, 2010 and 2009, the Organization had no uncertain tax positions requiring accrual.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: FORM 990, PART III, LINE 4A - PROGRAM SERVICE ACCOMPLISHMENTS
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: UNITED WAY OF KING COUNTY IS COMMITTED TO CHANGING OUR COMMUNITY FOR THE BETTER IN FUNDAMENTAL LASTING WAYS BY ENHANCING THE ABILITY OF INDIVIDUALS TO CARE FOR ONE ANOTHER. WE ARE ABLE TO PLAY THIS ROLE BECAUSE OF THE TRUST THE COMMUNITY HAS IN UNITED WAY OF KING COUNTY'S EXPERTISE, EFFICIENCY, AND RESULTS. WE DEEPLY UNDERSTAND OUR COMMUNITY, ITS PEOPLE AND ITS CHALLENGES. WITH A SOLID GRASP OF THE ISSUES, UNITED WAY OF KING COUNTY IS ABLE TO SHAPE AN EFFECTIVE RESPONSE. WE'RE ACQUAINTED WITH THE NETWORK OF SERVICE PROVIDERS IN OUR REGION AND WE KNOW WHO HAS THE CAPACITY AND TRACK RECORD TO BRING ABOUT CHANGE. IN ADDITION TO EXPERTISE, UNITED WAY OF KING COUNTY STANDS FOR EFFICIENCY. WE PUT 97 CENTS OF EVERY DONATED DOLLAR INTO COMMUNITY PROGRAMS. ACHIEVEMENTS: 32,886 VOLUNTEERS CONNECTED TO SERVICE PROJECTS. UNITED WAY OF KING COUNTY IS A CENTRAL HUB OF VOLUNTEERING IN OUR REGION. 14,000 FREE TAX RETURNS FILED BRINGING $19.7 MILLION IN FEDERAL REFUNDS BACK INTO OUR COMMUNITY. 5,213 OLDER ADULTS MAINTAINED THE HIGHEST POSSIBLE QUALITY OF LIFE. 33,200 YOUTH STRENGTHENED ACADEMIC SKILLS. 2,556 SURVIVORS OF DOMESTIC VIOLENCE GIVEN ASSISTANCE AND ACCESS TO TOOLS THAT SUPPORT PERSONAL SAFETY SO THEY CAN BEGIN TO HEAL. 2 MILLION POUNDS OF FOOD PROVIDED FOR HUNGER RELIEF ORGANIZATIONS, INCLUDING FRESH PRODUCE AND INFANT FORMULA. 4,500 FAMILIES CONNECTED TO BASIC FOOD (FOOD STAMPS) AND OTHER PUBLIC BENEFITS. 19,509 PEOPLE PREPARED TO TAKE APPROPRIATE ACTION IN THE EVENT OF AN EMERGENCY OR DISASTER.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: FORM 990, PART III, LINE 4B - PROGRAM SERVICE ACCOMPLISHMENTS
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: UNITED WAY OF KING COUNTY IS ABLE TO ACHIEVE MEANINGFUL RESULTS IN THE COMMUNITY BECAUSE WE PINPOINT THE AREAS WHERE WE CAN MAKE THE BIGGEST IMPACT. INSTEAD OF MERELY ADDRESSING THE SYMPTOMS OF A PROBLEM, WE GO DEEPER TO FIND THE ROOT CAUSES AND DETERMINE HOW WE CAN CREATE SOLUTIONS. OUR PRIORITY TO END HOMELESSNESS IN KING COUNTY IS A GOOD ILLUSTRATION OF THIS. WE KNOW THAT TO REALLY END HOMELESSNESS WE MUST PREVENT PEOPLE FROM BECOMING HOMELESS, AND MOVE PEOPLE INTO HOUSING THAT WILL PROVIDE THE STRUCTURE AND SUPPORT THEY NEED TO BECOME STABLE AND SELF-SUFFICIENT. PERMANENT SUPPORTIVE HOUSING IS A PROVEN STRATEGY THAT HAS SAVED LIVES, AND SAVES OUR COMMUNITY TENS OF THOUSANDS OF DOLLARS IN AVOIDING COSTS FOR VISITS TO THE EMERGENCY ROOM, THE SOBERING CENTER AND THE JAIL SYSTEM. ADDITIONALLY, UNITED WAY FUNDING IS LEVERAGING SUBSTANTIAL ADDITIONAL DOLLARS FROM THE CITY OF SEATTLE, KING COUNTY, THE SEATTLE HOUSING AUTHORITY AND THE KING COUNTY HOUSING AUTHORITY TO TRULY END HOMELESSNESS. ACHIEVEMENTS: 14,337 PEOPLE AT RISK OF BECOMING HOMELESS RETAINED STABLE HOUSING. 16,300 PEOPLE RECEIVED EMERGENCY SHELTER AND WERE SHIELDED FROM THE DANGER OF THE STREETS. 4,733 HOMELESS INDIVIDUALS MOVED INTO TRANSITIONAL HOUSING. 288 NEW UNITS OF SUPPORTIVE HOUSING WERE OPENED.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: FORM 990, PART III, LINE 4C - PROGRAM SERVICE ACCOMPLISHMENTS
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: UNITED WAY OF KING COUNTY IS COMMITTED TO A COMMUNITY THAT THRIVES BOTH NOW AND FAR INTO THE FUTURE. HENCE, A KEY PRIORITY FOR US IS TO ENSURE THAT EVERY CHILD IN OUR REGION, REGARDLESS OF INCOME, NEIGHBORHOOD OR BACKGROUND, HAS THE CHANCE TO MAKE THE STRONGEST POSSIBLE START. SINCE A GROWING BODY OF RESEARCH INDICATES THAT THE AGES OF BIRTH TO AGE 6 ARE PIVOTAL TO DEVELOPMENT SOCIALLY, EMOTIONALLY AND COGNITIVELY, MUCH OF OUR EMPHASIS IS ON PROGRAMS THAT MAKE THESE EARLY YEARS AS RICH AND NURTURING AS POSSIBLE. ACHIEVEMENTS: 6,370 PARENTS LEARNED NEW SKILLS FROM EARLY LEARNING TO HELP THEIR CHILDREN DEVELOP THE SOCIAL, INTELLECTUAL AND EMOTIONAL SKILLS FOR HEALTHY DEVELOPMENT. 2,299 CHILDREN MET KEY DEVELOPMENTAL MILESTONES TO PREPARE THEM TO ENTER SCHOOL READY TO LEARN. 2,653 KIDS WITH DEVELOPMENTAL DELAYS WERE HELPFUL TO IMPROVE THEIR PHYSICAL, COGNITIVE AND SOCIAL-EMOTIONAL FUNCTIONING THROUGH EARLY INTERVENTION. 25 CHILD CARE PROVIDERS SUCESSFULLY REACHED THE NATIONAL "COMMITTED TO QUALITY" MILESTONE OR FULL ACCREDITATION TO PROVIDE HIGH QUALITY CHILDCARE LEADING TO CHILDREN'S READY TO ENTER SCHOOL PREPARED TO LEARN.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: SCHEDULE I, PART IV - SUPPLEMENTAL INFORMATION
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: UNITED WAY OF KING COUNTY (UWKC) RESPECTS THE DESIRE OF DONORS TO CHOOSE TO DESIGNATE THEIR CONTRIBUTION. SEVERAL OPTIONS ARE AVAILABLE TO ACCOMMODATE DONORS' CHOICES. A DONOR MAY GIVE A CONTRIBUTION TO UNITED WAY TO SUPPORT UWKC PROGRAMS AND PRIORITIES. A DONOR MAY DESIGNATE HIS/HER CONTRIBUTION TO A UNITED WAY PARTNER AGENCY. THIS CONTRIBUTION WILL BE GIVEN TO THE AGENCY IN ADDITION TO ALLOCATIONS FROM UWKC. A DONOR MAY DESIGNATE HIS/HER CONTRIBUTION TO ANY 501(C)(3) ORGANIZATION. A DONOR MAY DESIGNATE HIS/HER CONTRIBUTION TO ANY UNITED WAY OF THE UNITED STATES. UWKC RESERVES THE RIGHT TO COLLECT A FEE FOR PROCESSING DONOR-DESIGNATED DOLLARS, UWKC RESERVES THE DISCRETION TO DECLINE TO ACCEPT PARTICULAR DONOR-DESIGNATED DOLLARS. UWKC MAY ENCOUNTER CIRCUMSTANCES WHERE IT MUST HOLD OR FREEZE DONOR-DESIGNATED DOLLARS DUE TO LEGAL COMPULSION, THREAT OF COMPULSION, OR OTHER REASONS. THOSE UNITED WAY OF KING COUNTY DOLLARS GRANTED DIRECTLY TO AGENCIES ARE MONITORED THROUGH ROUTINE REPORTING OF GRANTEES, AUDIT INFORMATION AND REVIEW, AND PERIODIC SITE VISITS.
